🧠 PanjoCoin (PNJC) — Formal Tokenomics Mathematical Model v1.0

---

# 1. 📦 Basic Model Variables

Let:

* ( S_0 ) — total fixed supply
* ( t \in [0, T] ) — time (measured in months or blocks)
* ( N ) — number of allocation categories
* ( A_i ) — allocation share of category *i*

### Normalization condition:

[
\sum_{i=1}^{N} A_i = 1
]

---

# 2. 🪙 Supply Model (Emission Structure)

PanjoCoin uses a **fixed-supply, non-inflationary model**:

[
S(t) = S_0
]

However, circulating supply is time-dependent:

[
C(t) = \sum_{i=1}^{N} V_i(t)
]

where:

* ( C(t) ) — circulating supply at time *t*
* ( V_i(t) ) — unlocked supply from category *i*

---

# 3. 🔓 Vesting / Unlock Model (Core CertiK Component)

Each allocation category follows a deterministic vesting function.

## 📌 General Vesting Function

[
V_i(t) =
\begin{cases}
0, & t < t_{cliff,i} \
A_i S_0 \cdot \frac{t - t_{cliff,i}}{t_{end,i} - t_{cliff,i}}, & t_{cliff,i} \le t < t_{end,i} \
A_i S_0, & t \ge t_{end,i}
\end{cases}
]

---

## 📊 Interpretation:

* Before cliff → no unlock
* During vesting → linear release
* After completion → fully unlocked

---

# 4. ⛓ Token Allocation Model

The total supply is distributed across predefined categories:

| Category        | Allocation |
| --------------- | ---------- |
| Liquidity       | ( A_1 )    |
| Team            | ( A_2 )    |
| Staking Rewards | ( A_3 )    |
| Airdrop         | ( A_4 )    |
| Treasury        | ( A_5 )    |

### Vector form:

[
\mathbf{A} =
\begin{bmatrix}
A_1 \
A_2 \
A_3 \
A_4 \
A_5
\end{bmatrix}
\quad \text{where} \quad \sum A_i = 1
]

---

# 5. 📈 Circulating Supply Function

[
C(t) = S_0 \cdot \sum_{i=1}^{N} A_i \cdot f_i(t)
]

where:

[
f_i(t) =
\begin{cases}
0, & t < t_{cliff,i} \
\frac{t - t_{cliff,i}}{t_{end,i} - t_{cliff,i}}, & t_{cliff,i} \le t < t_{end,i} \
1, & t \ge t_{end,i}
\end{cases}
]

---

# 6. 📉 Unlock Velocity (Risk Metric)

CertiK-style risk analysis focuses on unlock velocity:

[
U(t) = \frac{dC(t)}{dt}
]

Interpretation:

* High ( U(t) ) → inflation pressure
* Low ( U(t) ) → stable supply dynamics
* Controlled slope → institutional-grade tokenomics

