# 7. 🧾 Formal Allocation Proof

## ✅ Theorem: Supply Conservation

### Statement:

Total circulating supply never exceeds total supply:

[
\forall t: \quad C(t) \le S_0
]

---

## Proof:

Starting from definition:

[
C(t) = \sum_{i=1}^{N} V_i(t)
]

Since:

[
V_i(t) \le A_i S_0
]

Then:

[
C(t) \le \sum_{i=1}^{N} A_i S_0
]

Factorization:

[
C(t) \le S_0 \sum_{i=1}^{N} A_i
]

Using normalization:

[
\sum_{i=1}^{N} A_i = 1
]

Therefore:

[
C(t) \le S_0
]

✔ QED

